# NS0318 Sync Error: Could Not Import Items Due to Permissions Error

If you see the error message **“NS0318 Sync Error: Could not import items due to permissions error. Please update your NetSuite bundle version.”**, it usually means the **Expensify Connect bundle** in NetSuite is out of date.

This error most commonly appears when exporting an **invoice** from Expensify to NetSuite.

---

## Why the NS0318 Sync Error Happens

The NS0318 sync error occurs when:

- The **Expensify Connect bundle** in NetSuite is not updated to the latest version, and  
- You are exporting an **invoice** from Expensify.

An outdated bundle can cause permission mismatches that prevent items from importing correctly into NetSuite.

---

## How to Fix the NS0318 Sync Error

### Step 1: Confirm What You’re Exporting

In Expensify, confirm whether you are exporting:

- An **invoice**, or  
- An **expense report**

If you are exporting an expense report:

- You can ignore the NS0318 error.
- Manually refresh the page.
- Confirm the Workspace synced successfully.

If you are exporting an invoice, continue to Step two.

---

### Step 2: Update the Expensify Connect Bundle in NetSuite

In NetSuite:

1. Go to **Customization > SuiteBundler > Search & Install Bundles > List**.
2. Locate the **Expensify Connect bundle**.
3. Update it to the latest version.

After updating the bundle, return to Expensify and try exporting the invoice again.

---

### Step 3: Reconfirm the NetSuite Connection (If Needed)

If the Expensify Connect bundle is already on the latest version and the error continues, re-run the NetSuite connection steps to ensure everything is configured correctly:

[Connect to NetSuite](https://help.expensify.com/articles/new-expensify/connections/netsuite/Connect-To-NetSuite)

Carefully confirm that each step in the guide was completed.

---

# FAQ

## Does the NS0318 Sync Error affect expense report exports?

No. This error is primarily related to invoice exports. If you see it while exporting an expense report, you can refresh the page and confirm the Workspace synced successfully.

## Do I need NetSuite admin access to update the Expensify Connect bundle?

Yes. Updating bundles in NetSuite requires the appropriate NetSuite permissions.
